MEASUREMENTS AND COLOUR . Length 22.1 (Ƌ) or 22.3 mm ( ♀ ), width of midbody pro- and metazonae 2.5 and 3.6 mm (Ƌ) or 1.97 and 2.55 mm ( ♀ ), respectively. Live coloration light brown (
Fig. 16 A
); paraterga, legs and epiproct light yellow-brown, head and collum light brown, antennomere 7 blackish, collum and following terga each with a light brown triangle and a dark brown collar covering both pro- and metazonae. Coloration of alcohol material faded after one year of preservation to light brown, with a pattern of a dark brown band in pre-sulcus area on metazonae and a pair of paramedian, longitudinal, brown stripes dorsally both on pro- and metaterga; paraterga light red-brown, head brown, antennae, legs, venter and epiproct light yellow-brown ( Fig. 16 B–J ).

